Fgettyimages-1209292601.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5539x3693+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F14%2F33%2Fce0d5ee94565b17855b245cc14c5%2Fgettyimages-1209292601.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5539x3693+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F14%2F33%2Fce0d5ee94565b17855b245cc14c5%2Fgettyimages-1209292601.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5539x3693+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F14%2F33%2Fce0d5ee94565b17855b245cc14c5%2Fgettyimages-1209292601.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5539x3693+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F14%2F33%2Fce0d5ee94565b17855b245cc14c5%2Fgettyimages-1209292601.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5539x3693+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F14%2F33%2Fce0d5ee94565b17855b245cc14c5%2Fgettyimages-1209292601.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5539x3693+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F14%2F33%2Fce0d5ee94565b17855b245cc14c5%2Fgettyimages-1209292601.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5539x3693+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F14%2F33%2Fce0d5ee94565b17855b245cc14c5%2Fgettyimages-1209292601.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5539x3693+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F14%2F33%2Fce0d5ee94565b17855b245cc14c5%2Fgettyimages-1209292601.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5539x3693+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F14%2F33%2Fce0d5ee94565b17855b245cc14c5%2Fgettyimages-1209292601.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5539x3693+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F14%2F33%2Fce0d5ee94565b17855b245cc14c5%2Fgettyimages-1209292601.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5539x3693+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F14%2F33%2Fce0d5ee94565b17855b245cc14c5%2Fgettyimages-1209292601.jpg" class="img" alt="A brown-furred dog looks out from a cage at an animal shelter." fetchpriority="high" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 A dog looks out from a cage at Auntie Ju's shelter for stray dogs on the outskirts of Bangkok on April 6, 2020.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          MLADEN ANTONOV/AFP via Getty Images/AFP                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Our pets — whether dogs, cats, birds, reptiles, or any other animal — enrich our lives and fill our homes with love. Millions of animals are waiting in one of the many shelters in the U.S. for the opportunity to go to a fur-ever home. This is why &lt;a href="https://www.americanhumane.org/blog/national-adopt-a-shelter-pet-day/" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;u&gt;National Adopt a Shelter Pet Day&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, on April 30, exists to help bring awareness and help them get adopted. To celebrate, NPR wants to know how your pet changed your life. Your story could help influence someone to take the next step in their pet adoption journey.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;If you have a shelter pet that has impacted your life, please share your story with us via the form below. You could be featured in the &lt;em&gt;Up First&lt;/em&gt; newsletter on April 27. You can also share a photo and upload your answers as a voice memo. &lt;strong&gt;Please submit responses by April 9.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;p&gt;See some of your responses — and get the news you need to start your day — by &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/newsletter/news" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;u&gt;subscribing to our newsletter&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-58279-100" class="bucketwrap statichtml"&gt;             &lt;iframe src="https://npr.formstack.com/forms/animal_pet_rescue_adoption_shelter" title="Formstack Form" width="100%" height="1200"&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;     &lt;!-- END ID="RESG-S1-58279-100" CLASS="BUCKETWRAP STATICHTML" --&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Your submission will be governed by our general &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/about-npr/179876898/terms-of-use" target="_blank"&gt;Terms of Use&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; and &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/about-npr/179878450/privacy-policy" target="_blank"&gt;Privacy Policy&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;. As the Privacy Policy says, we want you to be aware that there may be circumstances in which the exemptions provided under law for journalistic activities or freedom of expression may override privacy rights you might otherwise have.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
