      <title>Trump doesn't rule out seeking 3rd term. And, a revamp of the Smithsonian Institution</title>
      <author>Brittney Melton</author>
      <link>https://www.npr.org/2025/03/31/g-s1-57273/up-first-newsletter-trump-third-term-smithsonian-institution-overhaul-myanmar-earthquake</link>
      <comments>https://text.npr.org/2025/03/31/g-s1-57273/up-first-newsletter-trump-third-term-smithsonian-institution-overhaul-myanmar-earthquake</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.npr.org/2025/03/31/g-s1-57273/up-first-newsletter-trump-third-term-smithsonian-institution-overhaul-myanmar-earthquake</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 31 Mar 2025 10:59:43 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div id="storytext" class="storytext storylocation linkLocation"&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Good morning. You're reading the Up First newsletter. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/newsletter/news" target="_blank"&gt;Subscribe&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; here to get it delivered to your inbox, and &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/podcasts/510318/up-first/" target="_blank"&gt;listen&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; to the Up First podcast for all the news you need to start your day.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Today's top stories&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;President Trump says he isn't ruling out the possibility of seeking a third term in office. &lt;/strong&gt;Yesterday, Trump told NBC News he "&lt;a href="http://www.npr.org/2025/03/30/g-s1-57231/trump-third-term" target="_blank"&gt;was not joking&lt;/a&gt;" about serving another term and that "there are methods" that would allow him to do so. He did not elaborate on those methods. The Constitution mandates a two-term limit for the president.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-57232" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 4736;         --source-height: 2664;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4736x2664+0+247/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7e%2F53%2F698bfe414a12ae3c0710b1941df7%2Fap25087774244367.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4736x2664+0+247/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7e%2F53%2F698bfe414a12ae3c0710b1941df7%2Fap25087774244367.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4736x2664+0+247/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7e%2F53%2F698bfe414a12ae3c0710b1941df7%2Fap25087774244367.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4736x2664+0+247/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7e%2F53%2F698bfe414a12ae3c0710b1941df7%2Fap25087774244367.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4736x2664+0+247/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7e%2F53%2F698bfe414a12ae3c0710b1941df7%2Fap25087774244367.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4736x2664+0+247/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7e%2F53%2F698bfe414a12ae3c0710b1941df7%2Fap25087774244367.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4736x2664+0+247/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7e%2F53%2F698bfe414a12ae3c0710b1941df7%2Fap25087774244367.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4736x2664+0+247/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7e%2F53%2F698bfe414a12ae3c0710b1941df7%2Fap25087774244367.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4736x2664+0+247/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7e%2F53%2F698bfe414a12ae3c0710b1941df7%2Fap25087774244367.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4736x2664+0+247/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7e%2F53%2F698bfe414a12ae3c0710b1941df7%2Fap25087774244367.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4736x2664+0+247/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7e%2F53%2F698bfe414a12ae3c0710b1941df7%2Fap25087774244367.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4736x2664+0+247/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7e%2F53%2F698bfe414a12ae3c0710b1941df7%2Fap25087774244367.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4736x2664+0+247/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7e%2F53%2F698bfe414a12ae3c0710b1941df7%2Fap25087774244367.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4736x2664+0+247/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7e%2F53%2F698bfe414a12ae3c0710b1941df7%2Fap25087774244367.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4736x2664+0+247/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7e%2F53%2F698bfe414a12ae3c0710b1941df7%2Fap25087774244367.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4736x2664+0+247/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7e%2F53%2F698bfe414a12ae3c0710b1941df7%2Fap25087774244367.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4736x2664+0+247/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7e%2F53%2F698bfe414a12ae3c0710b1941df7%2Fap25087774244367.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4736x2664+0+247/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F7e%2F53%2F698bfe414a12ae3c0710b1941df7%2Fap25087774244367.jpg" class="img" alt="President Donald Trump arrives on Air Force One at Palm Beach International Airport, Friday, March 28, 2025, in West Palm Beach, Fla. (AP Photo/Manuel Balce Ceneta)" loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 President Donald Trump arrives on Air Force One at Palm Beach International Airport, Friday, March 28, 2025, in West Palm Beach, Fla. (AP Photo/Manuel Balce Ceneta)                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Manuel Balce Ceneta/AP/AP                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧 &lt;strong&gt;There is something of a movement among Trump's most avid supporters promoting the idea of a third term&lt;/strong&gt;, NPR's Tamara Keith tells &lt;em&gt;Up First&lt;/em&gt;. A Republican congressman even introduced a constitutional amendment three days into Trump's second term to pave the way for a third. Keith says there's a political reason for Trump to pursue this. Unless something dramatic happens, the clock is ticking on his power. Members of his party will soon run to replace him and he will be seen as a lame duck, she says. Teasing a third term &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=1241892536:1268673697" target="_blank"&gt;could potentially extend his influence&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Trump has issued an executive order targeting the Smithsonian Institution, aiming to restore the "truth and sanity to American history."&lt;/strong&gt; The order includes &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/03/27/nx-s1-5342914/smithsonian-president-trump-executive-order" target="_blank"&gt;provisions seeking to reinstate monuments&lt;/a&gt;, memorials and statues that were removed or altered since January 2020. In response, Smithsonian Secretary Lonnie Bunch told staff in an email that it would continue to &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/03/28/nx-s1-5343524/smithsonian-trump-executive-order" target="_blank"&gt;employ internal review processes&lt;/a&gt; and that their work "will be shaped by the best scholarship, free of partisanship, to help the American public better understand the nation's history, challenges and triumphs." &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧&lt;strong&gt; NPR's Isabella Gomez Sarmiento says one big question is which monuments would be put back up. &lt;/strong&gt;Many of the sites that saw changes to monuments were &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=1241892536:1268673697" target="_blank"&gt;on land controlled by&lt;/a&gt; municipalities and state governments, according to Seth Levi of the Southern Poverty Law Center, a legal and advocacy group. This land isn't controlled by the Department of the Interior, which is tasked with reviewing monuments by Trump's executive order.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Myanmar's military authorities say the death toll from Friday's 7.7 magnitude earthquake has climbed to over 1,700. &lt;/strong&gt;That number is expected to rise as the window to find survivors is closing. Foreign assistance has started to arrive, but efforts have been stifled by buckled roads, collapsed bridges and downed cell towers. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧&lt;strong&gt; Lack of heavy equipment and personnel has hampered efforts to rescue those trapped underneath the rubble&lt;/strong&gt;, says NPR's Michael Sullivan. Rescue workers say the smell of death is overpowering. Rescue teams from China, India and Russia have arrived in the country, but the airport is closed to large aircraft and much of the foreign assistance is being flown around 350 miles south to Yangon. Trump said on Friday that the U.S. would also &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=1241892536:1268673697" target="_blank"&gt;help in assistance efforts&lt;/a&gt;. The USAID, which played a large role in disaster relief in the past, has been gutted by the Trump administration in recent weeks.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;➡️ &lt;strong&gt;See photos&lt;/strong&gt; of the &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/03/29/g-s1-57186/photos-see-the-aftermath-of-the-earthquake-in-myanmar-and-thailand" target="_blank"&gt;aftermath of the earthquake&lt;/a&gt; in Myanmar and Thailand.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;       &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Picture show&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-56427" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 3000;         --source-height: 1688;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+157/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F66%2Fb5%2Fe73d997747a587a8600c261efdc3%2F250326-cherryblossoms-01.JPG 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+157/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F66%2Fb5%2Fe73d997747a587a8600c261efdc3%2F250326-cherryblossoms-01.JPG 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+157/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F66%2Fb5%2Fe73d997747a587a8600c261efdc3%2F250326-cherryblossoms-01.JPG 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+157/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F66%2Fb5%2Fe73d997747a587a8600c261efdc3%2F250326-cherryblossoms-01.JPG 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+157/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F66%2Fb5%2Fe73d997747a587a8600c261efdc3%2F250326-cherryblossoms-01.JPG 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+157/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F66%2Fb5%2Fe73d997747a587a8600c261efdc3%2F250326-cherryblossoms-01.JPG 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+157/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F66%2Fb5%2Fe73d997747a587a8600c261efdc3%2F250326-cherryblossoms-01.JPG 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+157/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F66%2Fb5%2Fe73d997747a587a8600c261efdc3%2F250326-cherryblossoms-01.JPG" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+157/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F66%2Fb5%2Fe73d997747a587a8600c261efdc3%2F250326-cherryblossoms-01.JPG 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+157/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F66%2Fb5%2Fe73d997747a587a8600c261efdc3%2F250326-cherryblossoms-01.JPG 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+157/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F66%2Fb5%2Fe73d997747a587a8600c261efdc3%2F250326-cherryblossoms-01.JPG 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+157/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F66%2Fb5%2Fe73d997747a587a8600c261efdc3%2F250326-cherryblossoms-01.JPG 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+157/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F66%2Fb5%2Fe73d997747a587a8600c261efdc3%2F250326-cherryblossoms-01.JPG 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+157/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F66%2Fb5%2Fe73d997747a587a8600c261efdc3%2F250326-cherryblossoms-01.JPG 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+157/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F66%2Fb5%2Fe73d997747a587a8600c261efdc3%2F250326-cherryblossoms-01.JPG 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+157/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F66%2Fb5%2Fe73d997747a587a8600c261efdc3%2F250326-cherryblossoms-01.JPG" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+157/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F66%2Fb5%2Fe73d997747a587a8600c261efdc3%2F250326-cherryblossoms-01.JPG" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+157/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F66%2Fb5%2Fe73d997747a587a8600c261efdc3%2F250326-cherryblossoms-01.JPG" class="img" alt="Gabriella Cardenas of North Potomac, Md., wears her quinceañera dress as she and her father, Boris Cardenas (holding dress), brother Jason Cardenas and mother Patty Cardenas move to a new spot along the Tidal Basin for a photo. " loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Gabriella Cardenas of North Potomac, Md., wears her quinceañera dress as she and her father, Boris Cardenas (holding dress), brother Jason Cardenas and mother Patty Cardenas move to a new spot along the Tidal Basin for a photo.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Tyrone Turner/WAMU                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The cherry blossoms in the nation's capital reached peak bloom this weekend, attracting scores of people to the approximately 3,800 cherry trees near the National Mall. But even two days before peak bloom, droves of people came out to see the spectacle. Last Wednesday, D.C.'s Tidal Basin was packed with a mixed scene of special occasions and everyday moments. People posed for photoshoots, families pushed their strollers along the blossoms and joggers weaved through the crowd. Check out these &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/the-picture-show/2025/03/27/g-s1-56443/cherry-blossoms-dc-tidal-basin" target="_blank"&gt;photos of the blossoms&lt;/a&gt; and see how people have been enjoying them.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;From our hosts&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;by &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/4080709/steve-inskeep" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Steve Inskeep&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;em&gt;Morning Edition &lt;/em&gt;and &lt;em&gt;Up First &lt;/em&gt;host&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;During a week in China, we glimpsed the high and low ends of its economy.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Global business leaders &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/03/24/nx-s1-5336184/beijings-china-development-forum-displays-tensions-with-the-u-s" target="_blank"&gt;spoke at the China Development Forum&lt;/a&gt;. China's premier, or prime minister, told them China is now a stable country that follows global rules — a dig at the United States with its &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/03/27/nx-s1-5336144/trumps-tariffs-on-china-left-some-winners-vietnam-is-one-of-them" target="_blank"&gt;near-weekly changes in tariff policy&lt;/a&gt;. He also promoted China's progress in building humanoid robots.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-57274" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 3024;         --source-height: 1701;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3024x1701+0+852/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F01%2Fc8%2F6610344b4ddfb0f0cf11b999d665%2Fimg-0862.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3024x1701+0+852/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F01%2Fc8%2F6610344b4ddfb0f0cf11b999d665%2Fimg-0862.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3024x1701+0+852/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F01%2Fc8%2F6610344b4ddfb0f0cf11b999d665%2Fimg-0862.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3024x1701+0+852/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F01%2Fc8%2F6610344b4ddfb0f0cf11b999d665%2Fimg-0862.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3024x1701+0+852/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F01%2Fc8%2F6610344b4ddfb0f0cf11b999d665%2Fimg-0862.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3024x1701+0+852/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F01%2Fc8%2F6610344b4ddfb0f0cf11b999d665%2Fimg-0862.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3024x1701+0+852/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F01%2Fc8%2F6610344b4ddfb0f0cf11b999d665%2Fimg-0862.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3024x1701+0+852/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F01%2Fc8%2F6610344b4ddfb0f0cf11b999d665%2Fimg-0862.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3024x1701+0+852/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F01%2Fc8%2F6610344b4ddfb0f0cf11b999d665%2Fimg-0862.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3024x1701+0+852/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F01%2Fc8%2F6610344b4ddfb0f0cf11b999d665%2Fimg-0862.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3024x1701+0+852/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F01%2Fc8%2F6610344b4ddfb0f0cf11b999d665%2Fimg-0862.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3024x1701+0+852/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F01%2Fc8%2F6610344b4ddfb0f0cf11b999d665%2Fimg-0862.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3024x1701+0+852/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F01%2Fc8%2F6610344b4ddfb0f0cf11b999d665%2Fimg-0862.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3024x1701+0+852/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F01%2Fc8%2F6610344b4ddfb0f0cf11b999d665%2Fimg-0862.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3024x1701+0+852/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F01%2Fc8%2F6610344b4ddfb0f0cf11b999d665%2Fimg-0862.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3024x1701+0+852/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F01%2Fc8%2F6610344b4ddfb0f0cf11b999d665%2Fimg-0862.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3024x1701+0+852/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F01%2Fc8%2F6610344b4ddfb0f0cf11b999d665%2Fimg-0862.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3024x1701+0+852/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F01%2Fc8%2F6610344b4ddfb0f0cf11b999d665%2Fimg-0862.jpg" class="img" alt="The lobby of the Xiaomi auto plant in Beijing." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 The lobby of the Xiaomi auto plant in Beijing.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Steve Inskeep/NPR                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;An executive at the Forum spoke of artificial intelligence. To the layman, AI means ChatGPT, but he said the real money was in AI's application to manufacturing.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;We sensed what the executive meant when we &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/03/28/nx-s1-5341204/we-visit-the-chinese-city-where-your-stuff-comes-from" target="_blank"&gt;toured a factory&lt;/a&gt; making trendy Xiaomi electric cars. Robotic machinery did most of the work: Crane-like arms moved parts around on the assembly line while self-driving vehicles moved items around the factory floor. A century ago, Henry Ford's famous River Rouge auto plant employed 100,000 people; this plant employs 2,000.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;At the low end, we &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/03/28/nx-s1-5341204/we-visit-the-chinese-city-where-your-stuff-comes-from" target="_blank"&gt;toured a factory&lt;/a&gt; consisting of 4,000 3-D printers, the kind you can buy on Amazon and use in your home. The printers are cranking out millions of plastic animals and other toys for the global market. The factory owner contends he's creating opportunities for young people like himself who are adrift in China's high-tech, high-powered economy, which faces high youth unemployment.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-56983" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 3000;         --source-height: 1688;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+156/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F85%2Fcf%2F85732f7147c18589ddfa4c647ef2%2Fselect-27.JPG 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+156/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F85%2Fcf%2F85732f7147c18589ddfa4c647ef2%2Fselect-27.JPG 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+156/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F85%2Fcf%2F85732f7147c18589ddfa4c647ef2%2Fselect-27.JPG 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+156/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F85%2Fcf%2F85732f7147c18589ddfa4c647ef2%2Fselect-27.JPG 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+156/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F85%2Fcf%2F85732f7147c18589ddfa4c647ef2%2Fselect-27.JPG 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+156/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F85%2Fcf%2F85732f7147c18589ddfa4c647ef2%2Fselect-27.JPG 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+156/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F85%2Fcf%2F85732f7147c18589ddfa4c647ef2%2Fselect-27.JPG 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+156/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F85%2Fcf%2F85732f7147c18589ddfa4c647ef2%2Fselect-27.JPG" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+156/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F85%2Fcf%2F85732f7147c18589ddfa4c647ef2%2Fselect-27.JPG 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+156/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F85%2Fcf%2F85732f7147c18589ddfa4c647ef2%2Fselect-27.JPG 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+156/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F85%2Fcf%2F85732f7147c18589ddfa4c647ef2%2Fselect-27.JPG 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+156/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F85%2Fcf%2F85732f7147c18589ddfa4c647ef2%2Fselect-27.JPG 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+156/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F85%2Fcf%2F85732f7147c18589ddfa4c647ef2%2Fselect-27.JPG 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+156/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F85%2Fcf%2F85732f7147c18589ddfa4c647ef2%2Fselect-27.JPG 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+156/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F85%2Fcf%2F85732f7147c18589ddfa4c647ef2%2Fselect-27.JPG 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+156/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F85%2Fcf%2F85732f7147c18589ddfa4c647ef2%2Fselect-27.JPG" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+156/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F85%2Fcf%2F85732f7147c18589ddfa4c647ef2%2Fselect-27.JPG" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3000x1688+0+156/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F85%2Fcf%2F85732f7147c18589ddfa4c647ef2%2Fselect-27.JPG" class="img" alt="Elizabeth Kenward, left, and “Rosie” Maxine Boeve giggle together during the Rosie the Riveter Congressional Gold Medal Commemoration at the World War II Museum in New Orleans, La., on Friday, March 21, 2025." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Elizabeth Kenward, left, and "Rosie" Maxine Boeve giggle together during the Rosie the Riveter Congressional Gold Medal Commemoration at the World War II Museum in New Orleans, La., on Friday,  March 21, 2025.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Emily Kask/for NPR                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;Eighteen Rosie the Riveters were &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/03/30/nx-s1-5332291/rosie-the-riveters-honored-for-service-in-wwii" target="_blank"&gt;honored as Congressional Gold Medal recipients&lt;/a&gt; at the National WWII Museum. The women were trailblazers, proving women could succeed in what was considered a man's job at the time.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;In a break with tradition, this year's White House Correspondents' dinner will not include a featured comedian. Amber Ruffin's appearance was &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/03/29/nx-s1-5344487/white-house-correspondents-dinner-amber-ruffin" target="_blank"&gt;canceled&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A babysitter in Kansas was checking for a "monster" under a child's bed and &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/03/28/nx-s1-5343618/babysitter-man-under-bed" target="_blank"&gt;came face-to-face with a male suspect&lt;/a&gt; hiding there.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
