 /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1920x1080+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F06%2F44%2F877d9aa642e196d5aa1c814784af%2Ftrishotnew.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1920x1080+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F06%2F44%2F877d9aa642e196d5aa1c814784af%2Ftrishotnew.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1920x1080+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F06%2F44%2F877d9aa642e196d5aa1c814784af%2Ftrishotnew.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1920x1080+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F06%2F44%2F877d9aa642e196d5aa1c814784af%2Ftrishotnew.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1920x1080+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F06%2F44%2F877d9aa642e196d5aa1c814784af%2Ftrishotnew.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1920x1080+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F06%2F44%2F877d9aa642e196d5aa1c814784af%2Ftrishotnew.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1920x1080+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F06%2F44%2F877d9aa642e196d5aa1c814784af%2Ftrishotnew.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1920x1080+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F06%2F44%2F877d9aa642e196d5aa1c814784af%2Ftrishotnew.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1920x1080+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F06%2F44%2F877d9aa642e196d5aa1c814784af%2Ftrishotnew.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1920x1080+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F06%2F44%2F877d9aa642e196d5aa1c814784af%2Ftrishotnew.jpg" class="img" alt="From left to right: Split Fiction, Monster Hunter Wilds, and Avowed." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 From left to right: Split Fiction, Monster Hunter Wilds, and Avowed.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Hazelight Studios, Capcom, Obsidian Entertainment                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Check out what &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/culture/" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NPR&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt; is watching, reading and listening to this weekend:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🍿 Movies:&lt;/strong&gt; A roadkill unicorn, a family of greedy pharmaceutical moguls and an innocent teenager are the key elements in &lt;em&gt;Death of a Unicorn&lt;/em&gt;, starring Paul Rudd and Jenna Ortega. This horror comedy and more are &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/03/27/nx-s1-5338803/movies-in-theaters-this-weekend" target="_blank"&gt;hitting theaters today&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;📺 TV:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/03/25/1240671746/in-dope-thief-brian-tyree-henry-messes-with-the-wrong-drug-lord" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Dope Thief&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;stars Brian Tyree Henry as a man who robs small-time drug dealers by posing as a DEA agent. His luck runs out when he messes with the wrong house. Listen to why &lt;em&gt;Pop Culture Happy Hour&lt;/em&gt; says &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=1240671746:1268342093" target="_blank"&gt;the crime thriller series stands out&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;📚 Books: &lt;/strong&gt;Amanda Knox's memoir &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/03/26/nx-s1-5311607/amanda-knox-free" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Free: My Search for Meaning&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt; goes beyond the events of her trial, imprisonment and eventual exoneration for the murder of her roommate and explores how she rebuilt her life. Knox's book is just one of the new releases this week. &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/03/25/nx-s1-5333662/new-books-amanda-knox-column-mccann-yoko-ono-wicked" target="_blank"&gt;Here are four other reads&lt;/a&gt; to add to your list.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🎵 Music: &lt;/strong&gt;British soul singer Cleo Sol made her long-awaited New York City debut, guiding fans in a spiritual healing. NPR's Sidney Madden says Sol is a rarity because she rejects the current business model in the music industry and instead focuses on art as a message of higher power. &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/03/26/g-s1-56034/cleo-sol-radio-city-music-hall-concert-review" target="_blank"&gt;Listen to some of her music here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🎮 Gaming:&lt;/strong&gt; From cooperative platformers to historical epics, NPR staff and contributors have rounded up the latest from the &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/03/14/g-s1-53341/best-video-games-split-fiction-monster-hunter" target="_blank"&gt;best and biggest games of 2025 so far&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-56523" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 3500;         --source-height: 1969;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3500x1969+0+182/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F80%2Fb6%2F72e131a74ed48c19657b45b5b8a6%2Fap20336707183784.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3500x1969+0+182/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F80%2Fb6%2F72e131a74ed48c19657b45b5b8a6%2Fap20336707183784.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3500x1969+0+182/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F80%2Fb6%2F72e131a74ed48c19657b45b5b8a6%2Fap20336707183784.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3500x1969+0+182/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F80%2Fb6%2F72e131a74ed48c19657b45b5b8a6%2Fap20336707183784.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3500x1969+0+182/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F80%2Fb6%2F72e131a74ed48c19657b45b5b8a6%2Fap20336707183784.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3500x1969+0+182/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F80%2Fb6%2F72e131a74ed48c19657b45b5b8a6%2Fap20336707183784.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3500x1969+0+182/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F80%2Fb6%2F72e131a74ed48c19657b45b5b8a6%2Fap20336707183784.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3500x1969+0+182/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F80%2Fb6%2F72e131a74ed48c19657b45b5b8a6%2Fap20336707183784.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3500x1969+0+182/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F80%2Fb6%2F72e131a74ed48c19657b45b5b8a6%2Fap20336707183784.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3500x1969+0+182/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F80%2Fb6%2F72e131a74ed48c19657b45b5b8a6%2Fap20336707183784.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3500x1969+0+182/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F80%2Fb6%2F72e131a74ed48c19657b45b5b8a6%2Fap20336707183784.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3500x1969+0+182/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F80%2Fb6%2F72e131a74ed48c19657b45b5b8a6%2Fap20336707183784.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3500x1969+0+182/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F80%2Fb6%2F72e131a74ed48c19657b45b5b8a6%2Fap20336707183784.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3500x1969+0+182/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F80%2Fb6%2F72e131a74ed48c19657b45b5b8a6%2Fap20336707183784.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3500x1969+0+182/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F80%2Fb6%2F72e131a74ed48c19657b45b5b8a6%2Fap20336707183784.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3500x1969+0+182/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F80%2Fb6%2F72e131a74ed48c19657b45b5b8a6%2Fap20336707183784.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3500x1969+0+182/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F80%2Fb6%2F72e131a74ed48c19657b45b5b8a6%2Fap20336707183784.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3500x1969+0+182/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F80%2Fb6%2F72e131a74ed48c19657b45b5b8a6%2Fap20336707183784.jpg" class="img" alt="The marquee of the Egyptian Theatre at the Sundance Film Festival in Park City, Utah on Jan. 28, 2020." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 The marquee of the Egyptian Theatre at the Sundance Film Festival in Park City, Utah on Jan. 28, 2020.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Arthur Mola/Invision/AP                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;The Sundance Film Festival &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/03/27/nx-s1-5342419/sundance-new-home-boulder-colorado" target="_blank"&gt;will move to Boulder, Colo.&lt;/a&gt;, in 2027. It has been in Utah for over 40 years.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;U.S. Customs and Border Protection said this week that seizures of raw eggs have &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/03/28/nx-s1-5342554/eggs-border-seizures-fentanyl" target="_blank"&gt;risen 48% at the borders&lt;/a&gt; compared to last year. The egg seizures are outpacing border officials' interception of fentanyl.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;South Korea has &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=nx-s1-5341514:nx-s1-5404806-1" target="_blank"&gt;admitted its agencies mishandled&lt;/a&gt; adoptions after an investigation sparked by hundreds of complaints from adoptees. It has been one of the top countries sending babies abroad for adoption for decades.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
